The paper deals with the Closest Vector Problem (CVP) on lattices, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and information theory. The paper also employs lattice point enumeration techniques and random sublattice restrictions, which are common tools in computational geometry and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
